</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[187,1399,770,973]" pageId="18" pageNumber="63">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Fennah, 1956" authorityName="Fennah" authorityYear="1956" box="[495,838,770,797]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Andes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lachesis">
<emphasis box="[495,670,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="63">Andes lachesis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fennah R. G." box="[677,838,770,797]" pageId="18" pageNumber="63" pagination="441 - 527" refId="ref9612" refString="Fennah R. G. 1956. Fulgoroidea from Southern China. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences 28 (4): 441 - 527." type="journal article" year="1956">
Fennah, 
<quantity box="[779,838,770,797]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.96824" pageId="18" pageNumber="63" unit="in" value="1956.0">1956</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in appearance, but differs in: (1) apical ventral margin of periandrium with a long spinose process, bending upwards, directed cephalad, parallel to periandrium (apical dorsal margin of periandrium with a spinose process in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fennah" authorityYear="1956" box="[1060,1188,841,867]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Andes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lachesis">
<emphasis box="[1060,1188,841,867]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="63">A. lachesis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); (2) basal ventral margin of periandrium with a bifurcated process (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fennah" authorityYear="1956" box="[774,902,876,902]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Andes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lachesis">
<emphasis box="[774,902,876,902]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="63">A. lachesis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without process in the same position); (3) endosoma lamellar, basal left side of dorsal margin with small teeth (endosoma coarsely shagreen or sub-fimbriate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fennah" authorityYear="1956" box="[383,510,946,973]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Andes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lachesis">
<emphasis box="[383,510,946,973]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="63">A. lachesis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
